summary: Realistic ENB Setting designed to work with Climates of Tamriel
descriptionHtml:
[color=red][size=4][b]I will NO LONGER be updating this file. Please see my new ENB over [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/34509]HERE [/url][/size][/color][/b] 

_________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

[color=yellow]
STANDARD DOF:[/color] Very similar to the same DOF Every other ENB Has. Bokeh DOF.
[color=yellow]DYNAMIC DOF:[/color] Brand New DOF, very similar to what one would see in a movie. Screen shots mimic the look of a Miniature Model Set or Poster Shoot.

[color=yellow]CHECK OUT THE FIRST FIVE MINUTES OF SKYRIM BELOW!!! WATCH IN HD!!![/color]
[b][u]Want your game to look like mine?[/u] Check out the Discussion Board (Next to the Forum Tab up above), Check out, \"Want your Game to look like mine, Start Here!!!\" Post. Also check out the Topic on the DOF and Lighting. THE DYNAMIC DOF IS UNLIKE Any before, so you need to understand it before use.[/b]

[img]http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8195/8140075599_770b8eba3b_c.jpg[/img]

[youtube]kPOHY5zhpHw[/youtube]

[img]http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8185/8140091204_17b0735eb6_c.jpg[/img]

[color=red][size=4][b]Rezerect Skyrim ENB[/b] - [i]Steamin661[/i][/size][/color]

[i][b]UPDATED 10/30/12[/b][/i]
[i]VERSION: 3[/i]: [color=yellow] Huge Performance Increase, Vibrant Color for Trees, Deep Color for Water and Sky, AND a [u]GROUNDBREAKING DOF to give the most realistic experience every seen in Skyrim!!! Guaranteed!!! There is an optional DOF as well, standard Bohken. PLEASE See below for further info on the DOF[/u]. [/color]

[color=yellow]**Works with or without Climates of Tamriel**[/color]

[b][u][i]!!! FOR THE RIGHT COT SETTINGS; MAKE SURE AND READ THE REQUIREMENTS AND INSTALLATION SECTION !!![/u][/b][/i]
[color=yellow] I have updated COT Settings for V.3 ; see below![/color]

[b][u][i]If you are not using COT, I HIGHLY Recommend you use both:
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/9930]Revamped Exterior Fog [/url]
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/9571]Remove Ambient Interior Fog [/url][/i][/u][/b]

[color=red][size=3][b][i]PLEASE ENDORSE IF YOU LIKE[/i][/b][/size][/color]

[color=yellow]**SEE BELOW FOR TESTIMONIALS, VIDEOS AND PICTURES**[/color]


[color=teal][size=4][i][b][u]OVERVIEW[/u][/b][/i][/size][/color]

ENB Setting designed around [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/17802]Climates of Tamriel [/url]

Works well with both [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/17605]Claralux [/url]and [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/18916]Lanterns of Skyrim [/url](I dont recomend using both, as many lights will overlap); as well as [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/24460]Supreme and Volumetric Fog[/url] (NONE OF THESE MODS ARE NEEDED TO RUN ENB; but add a great amount of value)

For optimal quality, I HIGHLY recomend using [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/11]STEPs[/url]; STEPs is the easiest and best way to take your Skyrim Experience from Zero to Hero while still maintaining stability with your game.

I have not tested without Climates of Tamriel, though I have been told by users it looks just as good, or better in some\'s opinion. Try and see!

 

[color=teal][size=4][b][u]FEATURES OF REZERECT SKYRIM[/u][/b][/size][/color]

[b][u]Days[/u][/b]: Bright and Vibrant

[b][u]Nights[/u][/b]: Dark and Realistic (Dark Forests are great)

[u][b]Dungeons[/b][/u]: Dark, Creepy and Realistic

[b][u]Interiors[/u][/b]: Warm and Realistic (Feel like you are actually walking through an old castle)

[u]YOU WILL NEED[/u] a torch or Candellight Spell to adventure; this ENB is not designed to give bright dungeons and nights.

I HIGHLY Recomend using this [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/8741]Torch Radius Mod [/url]to increase the torch radius to a much more realistic and workable torch light. ALSO, be sure and pick up [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/17416] Wearable Lanterns[/url]; help to light up the nights and interiors; there is really no reason to adventure without it!!!

**There is an optional \"No Letterbox\" File. Download the main file and then the optional file. And Overwrite. No more Letterbox :) **


[color=teal][size=4][b][u]ENB SPECS:[/u][/b][/size][/color]

-High Quality Bloom

-Blinding Sun with Godrays Effect

-Realistic Skin, Water, Metals

-[b]Realistic Groundbreaking DOF (Depth of Field)[/b]: [i]This DOF Will take some time getting used to. PLEASE Make sure you play for a minimum of 10min before making your decision; this is to allow your eyes to adjust (just like a 3D Movie). It will also help if you try it in different areas (i.e. Whiterun, Riverwood, Forest with Lots of Grass).[/i]

-Letter Box for a Cinematic Feel

-Rich Vibrant Colors

-SkyEffects: Starts, Moon, Clouds, etc.

-High Quality with Low PC Impact [color=yellow](If you are getting 40+ FPS Pre-ENB, You WILL BE able to run this)[/color]


[img] http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8323/8148385536_1da1818844_b.jpg [/img]
 

[color=teal][size=4][b][u]REQUIREMENTS AND INSTALLATION[/u][/b][/size][/color]

[i]There is no particular Order of Download and Install[/i]

[size=3]1[/size]. This ENB is based off of the most recent and stable version of ENB; ENBSeries v.0.119; need to download from [url=http://enbdev.com/mod_tesskyrim_v0119.htm]HERE[/url]

-The File will come with two versions: Wrapper and Injector. I recomend using the Wrapper version. If you have issues with this one, use the Injector (Not recomended).

-Copy the d3d9.dll file into your Skyrim Folder (Not the Data Folder)

-Do not copy any of the other files which come with the download, ONLY THE d3d9.dll file

 

[size=3]2[/size]. Download my Mod: Rezerect Skyrim ENB (See download section above)

-Copy all of the files and drop them in your Skyrim Folder (Same area you put the d3d9.dll file).

-Currently there is only the BASE Version Available. If people want a higher quality version, let me know, I can easily up the Quality (SSAO, Shadows, etc.)

 

[size=3]3[/size]. [color=yellow]HIGHLY RECOMMENDED[/color] - Download Climates of Tamriel [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/17802]HERE[/url].

    Climates of Tamriel Information:

     - I designed Rezerect Skyrim based around three optional settings from Climates of Tamriel:

[b]     - Interior Setting[/b]: [color=yellow]Warm Interiors (Warms the interiors... here your sign)[/color]

[b]     - Night Level[/b]:[color=yellow] Level 2 [/color]

[b]     - Dungeons[/b]:[color=yellow] Hardcore[/color]

 

[size=3]4[/size]. [color=yellow]OPTIONAL[/color] - Download Darker Dungeons Mod [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/12454]HERE[/url]; forces dungeons to incorporate Night Settings into the Dungeons. 


[size=3]5[/size]. [color=yellow]OPTIONAL[/color] - IF You want to take advantage of the [b]SMAA (Which is supported with this Mod)[/b]; download the file from [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/16233]HERE[/url]. Place the .dll file and other files into your Skyrim folder (Same place as the ENB Files).

    - To activate the SMAA, open up the enbseries.ini file, and right at the top of the file under PROXY you will see: EnableProxyLibrary=false /  InitProxyFunctions=false ; set both of these to True. 


[color=yellow][b]NOTICE:[/b] - If you haven\'t already done so, follow the information below:
NOT DOING SO WILL CAUSE UNWANTED COLORING AND LIGHTING

- Make sure you open your SkyrimPrefs.ini; once opened locate and change the following: 

bFloatPointRenderTarget=0 to 1 ----------> (i.e. bFloatPointRenderTarget=1).
bTreesReceiveShadows=0 to 1 ----------> (i.e. bTreesReceiveShadows=1)
bDrawLandShadows=0 to 1 ----------> (i.e. bDrawLandShadows=1)
bShadowsOnGrass=0 to 1 ----------> (i.e. bShadowsOnGrass=1) 

OPTIONAL:
Due to the high Contrast and Brightness during the day, it is possible that the map be very \"bleached out\"; to help with this, try removing the clouds on your map. Do this by opening up your Skyrim.ini and change:

[MapMenu]
sMapCloudNIF=0

If its not there, just add it under Map.[/color]


- If you need more info on installing and using ENB settings, check out [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/23765]SkyRealism\'s ENB Manual[/url], BEST STEP BY STEP GUIDE OUT THERE!!! This is also where I got my start!

- For a high quality Skyrim.ini and SkyrimPref.ini preset, be sure and check out [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/26076] Ewi\'s configuration [/url]

[img] http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8044/8148392734_bd357895b5_b.jpg [/img]

[color=teal][size=4][i][b][u]TESTIMONIALS[/u][/b][/i][/size][/color]

timcollier3615:
[i]“...I saw your mod and went through all of the installation instructions.
Guess what? It has to be one of THE BEST mods that I\'ve installed. I am so very pleased by how it has improved the game.
Thank you.”[/i]

blackrose678:
[i]\"This. This is the most beautiful preset for ENB. Thank you...\"[/i]

IndigoNeko:
[i]\"Looks good! It\'s definitely high-contrast, and the colors are VERY vivid in daytime. Feels like you\'ve put a lot of time and effort into your preset, and I\'ve got to say: the results are pretty good.\"[/i]

Narfo:
[i]\"...downloading and installed the files, and thought \"Holy crap, that\'s pretty.\" I\'ve never seen my Skyrim like this, and I don\'t think I\'m getting any fps loss.\"[/i]

Dougfunny3:
[i]\"This ENB is superb! Creates a really well balanced and realistic feel, and the dungeons are freakin scary for a change lol ... one of the best enb\'s ever made, seriously dude awesome job! Endorsed!\"[/i]

 

[color=teal][size=4][b][u]VIDEOSHARE OF REZERECT SKYRIM[/u][/b][/size][/color]
